<font color="#FF0000">WEARINESS</font><br>
<tt>Sun Feb  9  0:13:01 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
Did you notice how long it has been since anyone left<br>
a message at this site? There's a pretty good reason.<br>
Ask one of those who had to go one with life after losing<br>
a brother, husband, or son or daughter.<br><br>
My Ex is still suffering. But I came back. At least we<br>
got to face it together. It was a mother. I also get to<br>
visit a few of my friends wives on occasion. They have<br>
their new lives now.<br><br>
If you really know them, after they have a few drinks<br>
or after a Nam movie, look in their eyes. Only the ones<br>
that died paid a higher price. Them and the ones who had<br>
to deal with the load we Vets brought into our homes.<br><br>
I still love her for doing nothing more than being there<br>
for me. What a load a shit I get to live with and all<br>
those I get to associate with share.<br><br>
Ah well, It don't mean nothin.
<p><code>-- carnival@ont.com  (JJ the Boonirat) </code><p>


